genresAdvancedInfo.name: georgian folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre encompasses the rich and diverse folk music traditions of Georgia, including polyphonic singing, instrumental music, and dance. It varies widely depending on the region and ethnicity of the performers, but is generally characterized by complex harmonies, improvisation, and a deep connection to Georgian culture and history.
